title: The Wax Child by Olga Ravn review – a visceral tale of witchcraft
summary: The author of *The Employees* returns with a vivid exploration of 17th-century Denmark, highlighting themes of everyday sorcery and the strength of female solidarity. This new work offers an intensely poetic depiction of women's experiences during this historical period. The narrative intertwines magic and camaraderie, providing a rich tapestry of life in that era.
